{
  "_comment": [
    "Machine-readable domain model. Written alongside domain-model.md.",
    "Relationships between classes are NOT declared explicitly — they are inferred by scanning",
    "property 'type', operation 'params', 'returns', and 'collaborators' for class names that",
    "exist elsewhere in this file. A class name appearing in any of those fields implies a",
    "dependency from the containing class toward the referenced one.",
    "Glossary-term-to-class mapping: when a domain-language term becomes a class, its text",
    "bullets map to properties (noun-valued bullets) or operations (verb-valued bullets).",
    "Visibility: 'public' is the default; use 'private' only for methods prefixed with '-' in",
    "the markdown class block. Properties have no visibility distinction.",
    "Constructor: list param types only, no param names. Omit (empty array or null) for classes",
    "that have no constructor (factory, pre-defined instances).",
    "Collaborators: hidden domain types used inside an operation but absent from params/returns.",
    "Invariants: declarative rules; use 'must', 'cannot', 'only if' phrasing."
  ],
  "module": "ModuleName",
  "scope": "bounded slice or engagement scope",
  "core_domain": {
